{{Citation}}
[[File:Talus_Tralus_EotECR.png|250px|thumb|The Double Worlds, Talus and Tralus]]
{{Quote|Talus and Tralus are called the Double Worlds because they are just the same size as each other. They orbit around each other. Centerpoint Station is in the balance point. the barycenter, between Talus and Tralus.|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="AaC">''[[Ambush at Corellia]]''</ref>}}
The '''Double Worlds''' was a phrase used to refer to the [[Double planet/Legends|double planets]] [[Talus/Legends|Talus]] and [[Tralus/Legends|Tralus]], which orbited [[Centerpoint Station]] as it orbited the star [[Corell/Legends|Corell]] in the [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]]. '''Double Worlders''' was the name given to citizens of either [[Planet/Legends|world]].

They were two of the [[Five Brothers/Legends|Five Brothers]]. It was believed that the [[Celestial/Legends|Celestials]] moved the planets into [[Corell/Legends|Corell's]] orbit from other places in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], along with three other planets; all kept in place by the [[Centerpoint Station]].

In [[500 BBY/Legends|500 BBY]], the [[Federation of the Double Worlds]] was founded—the government of Talus and Tralus. The Federation capital is [[Dearic/Legends|Dearic]] on [[Talus/Legends|Talus]].

During the [[Corellian Crisis]] in [[18 ABY/Legends|18 ABY]], the [[Tralus and Talus Liberation Party]] advocated independence for both worlds.

